      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CAWBOURNE CALI (1) missed the frame and was safely held latest finishing 7th at Temora following on from a third place finish (30.65) at this track the start prior. Goes very well here at the trip finding the frame in each of five starts. Has performed well from this box with a win and two minor placings to his name from four starts. Can make amends. ELITE DOM (2) has a strong record this track and trip with three wins and three placings from nine starts. Placed last time (25.98) at Temora in a Grade 3/4, finishing third and beaten 4.5 lengths. Suited here and expected to run well. AUNTY MEEKA (4) recorded a NG win two back then missed the frame last time at Wentworth Park, but drawn Box 4 this time where she has three wins. Expecting sharp improvement this line-up. PELOPONNESE (5) cannot be left out after placing last start.",
